HEADWORD: Wing-handed
<hw>Wing"-hand`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the anterior limbs or hands adapted for flight, as the bats
and pterodactyls.</def>⟦br⟧
